ents and applications.\n\n---\n\n## ST-1.1 — Project Structure and Dependencies\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775902829483,"end":1775902829513}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775902829517,"sessionID":"ses_283f1a7caffeQb7fcaz5lxZdpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7c0e93ae0010B4l5lEbgM1Dwd","messageID":"msg_d7c0e6ca4001uX5hgqqM1pdyd5","sessionID":"ses_283f1a7caffeQb7fcaz5lxZdpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ### Component Diagram\n6: \n7: ```\n8: ┌─────────────────────┐\n9: │  User Application   │\n10: │  (Agent/Service)    │\n11: └──────────┬──────────┘\n12:            │\n13:            ▼\n14: ┌─────────────────────┐\n15: │ CodeInterpreter     │\n16: │ Client              │\n17: │(Sync & Async APIs)  │\n18: └──────────┬──────────┘\n19:            │\n20:      ┌─────┴─────┐\n21:      ▼           ▼\n22: ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐\n23: │ Session │ │ HTTP    │\n24: │ Manager │ │ Client  │\n25: └────┬────┘ └────┬────┘\n26:      │           │\n27:      ▼           ▼\n28: ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐\n29: │ Session │ │ Code    │\n30: │ State   │ │ Interpreter\n31: └─────────┘ │ Service │\n32:             └─────────┘\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ## Key Design Decisions\n36: \n37: ### Client Architecture\n38: - Single client class supporting both sync and async operations\n39: - Async client available as `AsyncCodeInterpreterClient`\n40: - Shared configuration and models between sync/async\n41: - Lazy initialization of HTTP client\n42: \n43: ### Session Management\n44: - Server-side session state management\n45: - Client-side session reference tracking\n46: - Automatic session cleanup on context exit\n47: - Optional auto-create on first execution\n48: \n49: ### HTTP Client Design\n50: - Use `httpx` for both sync and async HTTP operations\n51: - Configurable timeouts at client and request level\n52: - Automatic retries for transient failures\n53: - Connection pooling for efficiency\n54: \n55: ### Data Models\n56: - Pydantic v2 models for validation\n57: - Immutable result objects\n58: - Rich metadata for debugging\n59: - Type-safe throughout\n60: \n61: ### Error Handling\n62: - Custom exception hierarchy\n63: - Automatic retry with exponential backoff\n64: - Clear error messages with context\n65: - Graceful degradation\n66: \n67: ## Data Flow\n68: \n69: 1. User application calls `client.execute_code()`\n70: 2. Client ensures session exists (create if needed)\n71: 3. HTTP client sends POST to `/v1/execute`\n72: 4. Service executes code in sandbox\n73: 5. Result returned as JSON\n74: 6. Client parses into `ExecutionResult` model\n75: 7. User receives structured result object\n76: \n77: ## Security Considerations\n78: \n79: - API key stored securely, never logged\n80: - Session isolation between users\n81: - File access restricted to session workspace\n82: - Execution timeouts prevent resource exhaustion\n\n(End of file - total 82 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│  User Application   │\n│  (Agent/Service)    │\n└──────────┬──────────┘\n           │\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│ CodeInterpreter     │\n│ Client              │\n│(Sync & Async APIs)  │\n└──────────┬──────────┘\n           │\n     ┌─────┴─────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","time":{"start":1775902829487,"end":1775902829516}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775902829519,"sessionID":"ses_283f1a7caffeQb7fcaz5lxZdpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7c0e9b66001wqYA5tfsO6ywW0","messageID":"msg_d7c0e6ca4001uX5hgqqM1pdyd5","sessionID":"ses_283f1a7caffeQb7fcaz5lxZdpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Foundation\n4: - [ ] Create CodeInterpreterClient class structure\n5: - [ ] Define data model schemas using Pydantic\n6: - [ ] Implement HTTP client abstraction with httpx\n7: - [ ] Set up configuration management\n8: - [ ] Define custom exception hierarchy\n9: \n10: ## Phase 2: Session Management\n11: - [ ] Implement session creation\n12: - [ ] Implement session closure\n13: - [ ] Add context manager support\n14: - [ ] Implement auto-session creation\n15: - [ ] Add session lifecycle hooks\n16: \n17: ## Phase 3: Code Execution\n18: - [ ] Implement basic code execution\n19: - [ ] Add language parameter support\n20: - [ ] Implement timeout handling\n21: - [ ] Add input data injection\n22: - [ ] Handle execution results\n23: \n24: ## Phase 4: File Operations\n25: - [ ] Implement file upload\n26: - [ ] Implement file download\n27: - [ ] Add file listing\n28: - [ ] Handle binary and text files\n29: - [ ] Add file validation\n30: \n31: ## Phase 5: Async API\n32: - [ ] Create AsyncCodeInterpreterClient\n33: - [ ] Implement async session management\n34: - [ ] Implement async code execution\n35: - [ ] Implement async file operations\n36: - [ ] Add async context managers\n37: \n38: ## Phase 6: Error Handling & Testing\n39: - [ ] Implement retry logic with tenacity\n40: - [ ] Add comprehensive error handling\n41: - [ ] Write unit tests with mocks\n42: - [ ] Write integration tests\n43: - [ ] Add type checking with mypy\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation\n- [ ] Create CodeInterpreterClient class structure\n- [ ] Define data model schemas using Pydantic\n- [ ] Implement HTTP client abstraction with httpx\n- [ ] Set up configuration management\n- [ ] Define custom exception hierarchy\n\n## Phase 2: Session Management\n- [ ] Implement session creation\n- [ ] Implement session closure\n- [ ] Add context manager support\n- [ ] Implement auto-session creation\n- [ ] Add session lifecycle hooks\n\n## Phase 3: Code Execution\n- [ ] Implement basic code execution\n- [ ] Add language parameter support\n- [ ] Implement timeout handling","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/plan.md","time":{"start":1775902829490,"end":1775902829517}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775902829521,"sessionID":"ses_283f1a7caffeQb7fcaz5lxZdpE","part":{"id":"prt_d7c0ea4a5001gXR0qfOp1eiqTT","messageID":"msg_d7c0e6ca4001uX5hgqqM1pdyd5","sessionID":"ses_283f1a7caffeQb7fcaz5lxZdpE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: SDK CodeInterpreterClient (AR-027)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-027  \n6: **Module:** sdk-python  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Target:** `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/code_interpreter.py`\n10: \n11: This delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the CodeInterpreterClient SDK that provides programmatic access to the Code Interpreter service for secure sandboxed code execution.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Initialization and Configuration\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide `CodeInterpreterClient` to interact with the Code Interpreter service.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Initialize with default configuration\n22: - **GIVEN** no parameters provided\n23: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is instantiated\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL default to environment-based configuration\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Initialize with explicit configuration\n27: - **GIVEN** `base_url`, `api_key`, and optional `timeout` parameters\n28: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(...)` is instantiated\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL store these values for API calls\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Initialize with custom HTTP client\n32: - **GIVEN** a custom `http_client` implementing the HTTP interface\n33: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(http_client=...)` is instantiated\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided client instead of creating one\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Session Management\n39: \n40: The system SHALL manage Code Interpreter sessions with automatic lifecycle handling.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Create new session\n43: - **GIVEN** valid configuration\n44: - **WHEN** `create_session()` is called\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `Session` object with session_id\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Auto-create session on first execution\n48: - **GIVEN** no active session exists\n49: - **WHEN** `execute_code()` is called\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL automatically create a session before execution\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Close session explicitly\n53: - **GIVEN** an active session\n54: - **WHEN** `close_session(session_id)` is called\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL terminate the session and cleanup resources\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Context manager support\n58: - **GIVEN** a session created via context manager\n59: - **WHEN** exiting the context\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL automatically close the session\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Code Execution\n65: \n66: The system SHALL execute code in sandboxed environments and return structured results.\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Execute Python code\n69: - **GIVEN** Python source code as string\n70: - **WHEN** `execute_code(code, language=\"python\")` is called\n71: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the code and return `ExecutionResult`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Execute JavaScript code\n74: - **GIVEN** JavaScript source code\n75: - **WHEN** `execute_code(code, language=\"javascript\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL execute in Node.js environment and return results\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Execute Bash commands\n79: - **GIVEN** shell commands as string\n80: - **WHEN** `execute_code(code, language=\"bash\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL execute in bash shell and return output\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Execution with timeout\n84: - **GIVEN** `timeout=30` parameter\n85: - **WHEN** `execute_code(...)` is called\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL enforce the timeout and raise `TimeoutError` if exceeded\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Execution with input data\n89: - **GIVEN** `input_data` parameter with initial variables/files\n90: - **WHEN** `execute_code(...)` is called\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL make data available to the execution environment\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Result Handling\n96: \n97: The system SHALL return execution results in a structured format.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Successful execution result\n100: - **GIVEN** code executes successfully\n101: - **WHEN** execution completes\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL return `ExecutionResult` with stdout, stderr, exit_code=0\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Failed execution result\n105: - **GIVEN** code raises an exception or exits non-zero\n106: - **WHEN** execution completes\n107: - **THEN** it SHALL return `ExecutionResult` with exit_code != 0 and error details\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Result with artifacts\n110: - **GIVEN** code generates files/images\n111: - **WHEN** execution completes\n112: - **THEN** it SHALL return artifact URLs/paths in `ExecutionResult.artifacts`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Result with execution time\n115: - **GIVEN** any code execution\n116: - **WHEN** result is returned\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL include execution duration in milliseconds\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — File Operations\n122: \n123: The system SHALL support file upload and download for code execution.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Upload file for execution\n126: - **GIVEN** a local file path or file-like object\n127: - **WHEN** `upload_file(session_id, file_path)` is called\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the file and return file reference\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Download result file\n131: - **GIVEN** an artifact path from execution result\n132: - **WHEN** `download_file(session_id, file_path)` is called\n133: - **THEN** it SHALL return file content or save to specified path\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: List session files\n136: - **GIVEN** an active session\n137: - **WHEN** `list_files(session_id)` is called\n138: - **THEN** it SHALL return list of files in the session workspace\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Error Handling\n143: \n144: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully with meaningful exceptions.\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Authentication error\n147: - **GIVEN** invalid or missing API key\n148: - **WHEN** any API call is made\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `AuthenticationError` with clear message\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Session not found\n152: - **GIVEN** invalid or expired session_id\n153: - **WHEN** session operation is attempted\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `SessionNotFoundError`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Execution timeout\n157: - **GIVEN** code that exceeds timeout\n158: - **WHEN** `execute_code()` times out\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ExecutionTimeoutError`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Rate limit exceeded\n162: - **GIVEN** too many requests\n163: - **WHEN** API returns 429\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RateLimitError` with retry-after info\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Async API\n169: \n170: The system SHALL provide async versions of all operations.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Async session creation\n173: - **GIVEN** async client usage\n174: - **WHEN** `await client.create_session()` is called\n175: - **THEN** it SHALL return `AsyncSession` object\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Async code execution\n178: - **GIVEN** async client usage\n179: - **WHEN** `await client.execute_code()` is called\n180: - **THEN** it SHALL execute asynchronously and return result\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Async file operations\n183: - **GIVEN** async client usage\n184: - **WHEN** `await client.upload_file()` is called\n185: - **THEN** it SHALL perform upload asynchronously\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## Data Model Reference\n190: \n191: ### CodeInterpreterClient Class\n192: \n193: ```python\n194: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n195:     def __init__(\n196:         self,\n197:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n198:         api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n199:         timeout: float = 30.0,\n200:         http_client: Optional[HttpClient] = None,\n201:     ) -> None: ...\n202:     def create_session(self) -> Session: ...\n203:     def close_session(self, session_id: str) -> None: ...\n204:     def execute_code(\n205:         self,\n206:         code: str,\n207:         language: str = \"python\",\n208:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n209:         input_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n210:     ) -> ExecutionResult: ...\n211:     def upload_file(self, session_id: str, file_path: Union[str, Path, IO]) -> FileReference: ...\n212:     def download_file(self, session_id: str, file_path: str) -> bytes: ...\n213:     def list_files(self, session_id: str) -> List[FileInfo]: ...\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### ExecutionResult Class\n217: \n218: ```python\n219: class ExecutionResult:\n220:     stdout: str\n221:     stderr: str\n222:     exit_code: int\n223:     execution_time_ms: int\n224:     artifacts: List[Artifact]\n225:     metadata: Dict[str, Any]\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### Session Class\n229: \n230: ```python\n231: class Session:\n232:     session_id: str\n233:     created_at: datetime\n234:     expires_at: Optional[datetime]\n235:     language: Optional[str]\n236:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n237:     def __enter__(self) -> Session: ...\n238:     def __exit__(self, *args) -> None: ...\n239: ```\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## File Index\n244: \n245: | Path | Purpose |\n246: |------|---------|\n247: | `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation |\n248: | `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/models.py` | Data models (ExecutionResult, Session, etc.) |\n249: | `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/exceptions.py` | Custom exceptions |\n250: | `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/__init__.py` | SDK package exports |\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## Dependencies\n255: \n256: | Dependency | Purpose |\n257: |------------|---------|\n258: | `httpx>=0.25.0` | HTTP client for API calls |\n259: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation and models |\n260: | `tenacity>=8.0.0` | Retry logic |\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Integration Points\n265: \n266: | Component | Integration |\n267: |-----------|-------------|\n268: | Code Interpreter Service | REST API calls to `/v1/sessions`, `/v1/execute` |\n269: | Authentication | API key in Authorization header |\n270: | Session Store | Server-side session management |\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## Implementation Notes\n275: \n276: 1. **HTTP Client:** Use `httpx` for both sync and async operations\n277: 2. **Retry Logic:** Use `tenacity` for automatic retries on transient errors\n278: 3. **Session Management:** Support both explicit and automatic session handling\n279: 4. **Language Support:** Start with Python, extend to JavaScript and Bash\n280: 5. **Error Handling:** Custom exception hierarchy for different error types\n281: 6. **Timeouts:** Configurable per-request and global timeouts\n282: 7. **Type Hints:** Full type annotation support\n283: 8. **Context Managers:** Support `with` statement for session lifecycle\n\n(End of file - total 283 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: SDK CodeInterpreterClient (AR-027)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-027  \n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `python-sdk/agentcube/sdk/code_interpreter.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the CodeInterpreterClient SDK that provides programmatic access to the Code Interpreter service for secure sandboxed code execution.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — Initialization and Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide `CodeInterpreterClient` to interact with the Code Interpreter service.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775902829492,"end":1775902829519}}}}
